I will admit that I think I probably overstated in the first comment. But again, there is an amplification effect related to all the issues I raised. The overall point, though, was related to how quickly this is going to affect Florida. An inch of SLR doesn't just mean the ocean has risen an inch closer in elevation relative to your hotel on the Miami coast. All the combined factors are going to put your property at severe risk well within the lifetime of existing structures, probably to the point that large portions of Florida are not going to be insurable.



