Author::::KevinFinn
DateTime::::2016-02-24T18:07:40Z
Having a more powerful storm will generate a larger storm surge. That is not rocket science. That is also not what you said earlier. A higher sea level does not produce greater storms. A higher sea level does not produce a greater tide change - obviously it produces a higher tide, but if the sea level increases 1 foot and a normal high tide increases it by an additional foot, it will not now suddenly be 2.5 feet higher.



